Vice President Mike Pence visited Nebraska and Iowa to assess the damage caused by severe flooding and to offer support to affected families and communities. He expressed sympathy for those who lost their lives and praised the efforts of first responders and volunteers. Pence assured the governors and congressmen present that the federal government would expedite the states' requests for disaster declarations in order to provide resources for recovery. The Vice President emphasized the unity and resilience of the affected regions and pledged to help rebuild stronger than before.